headline: Alphabet Stock Sell-Off: 4 Reasons Why You Shouldn't Panic About Google Search
summary: Alphabet shares came under pressure after an Apple exec said they saw search queries decline for the first time.  Shares of Alphabet (NASDAQ: GOOGL) (NASDAQ: GOOG) sank after Apple executive Eddy Cue said that searches on Safari declined for the first time ever in April.  Cue attributed the decline to people using more artificial intelligence (AI) chatbots and predicted that AI search engines will eventually replace traditional search.

headline: Where Will Apple Stock Be in 1 Year?
summary: Apple said tariffs will cost the company $900 million in its second quarter.  The tariffs are adding significant uncertainty to the company's outlook.  The tech-heavy Nasdaq Composite is down 8% year to date as investors worry that President Trump's tariffs will impede technology companies' growth.
